# Build Outbound v1

## Step

Resolved when fleet→Joel delivery rides Chat SDK adapters for the
three platforms behind contract v2, shadow-running against the old
path with receipts compared, every send journaled, no silent drops —
and the neat-memory DM delivers through it as the proof consumer.
Cutover (retiring old outbound paths) stops for Joel with the shadow
receipts on the table.

## Worker result — outbound v1 (2026-07-16)

Status intentionally remains open. The steering session still owns daemon
wiring, supervised shadow cutover, and any old-path retirement.

Built:

- `@joelclaw/message-contract` contract v2 domain: versioned kinds and routing,
  branded `flowId`, teaching errors, outbound intent/event schemas, reaction and
  reply event schemas, and HATEOAS delivery receipts.
- One exact Chat SDK train at `4.34.0` for `chat`, Telegram, Slack, Discord, and
  memory state. `instance.ts` composes one Chat instance, Telegram polling with
  reaction updates, Slack Socket Mode, Discord only when its channel env is
  deliberately non-blank, Telegram `stopPolling`, Discord abort/restart, and a
  `startChatSdkRuntime()` seam for steering to wire into `daemon.ts` later.
- Contract-v2 send path: intent routing, mandatory Telegram signal-policy
  preflight, adapter DM/thread delivery, requested + terminal journal rows,
  platform-message-to-flow index, Slack-native reply threading, reply flow anchor
  reuse, receipt return, and an unwired `notify send` compat mapper.
- Flag-gated shadow comparison (`CHAT_SDK_OUTBOUND_SHADOW_ENABLED`, default
  off): SDK send + legacy preview + journaled field diff.

